				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">ptoing wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also, the chars can have 256, and then another 256 for sprites, right?</div><br />Yes.<br /><br />If you're doing CHR RAM, you can have more than 256 background tiles if some tiles are used only at the start of a level and others are used only at the end. There just has to be a 264-pixel (33-tile) gap between one tile and another tile that reuses its tile number.<br /><br />If you're worried about metatile bloat, you can have the game randomly pepper tiles in specific positions with alternate versions as the engine draws the map to video memory.</div>

