					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Don't necessarily assume your programmer will want to handle mid level tile switching, though. What Tepples described precludes using CHR ROM which has benefits that may better suit the game, for instance. (Similar things can be done with CHR ROM, but there are more conditions than the single tile swap that can be done with CHR RAM)<br /><br />I got the 183 tile count with Pyxel Edit by forgetting I had it set to hex. $183 = 387. They still don't match, but if it's not counting two 16x16 regions that are the same except for their palettes, that would probably explain it. (Different palettes <em>should</em> matter for metastructures.)</div>

					
